Q: Find first and last occurence of element in sorted array
Question Link: http://leetcode.com/problems/find-first-and-last-position-of-element-in-sorted-array/description/
Question Explanation: Given a sorted array and there are duplicates present and you need to find the x
and the x first and last occurence in the given sorted array.

T.C: 2*O(logN) S.C: O(1)

Approach: Use binary search to find x, but instead of stopping, keep moving left to get the first occurrence and 
right to get the last occurrence, while remembering the latest index where x was found.

You need to understand where x will be present whether it will be on left side or right side.
First occurence means left most one, so you will try to eliminate the right part and similar with the last occurence.

Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] searchRange(int[] arr, int x) {
        int res[] = new int[2];

        int n = arr.length;
        int low = 0;
        int high = n-1;
        int mid = low + (high-low)/2;
        int ans = -1;

        while(high >= low){
            if(arr[mid] >= x){
                if(arr[mid] == x) ans = mid;
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else low = mid + 1;
            mid = low + (high-low)/2;
        }

        res[0] = ans;
        ans = -1;

        low = 0;
        high = n-1;
        mid = low + (high-low)/2;

        while(high >= low){
            if(arr[mid] <= x){
                if(arr[mid] == x) ans = mid;
                low = mid + 1;
            }
            else high =  mid - 1;
            mid = low + (high-low)/2;
        }

        res[1] = ans;
        return res;
    }
}
